cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper is about improving the performance of slot filling, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a new deep learning model, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The model also enforces consistency between feature vectors, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses a slot filling dataset, which could be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision) since slot filling is often used in image recognition tasks.
